      • synchronousReadAll

        HTTPMessage<T> synchronousReadAll()
                           throws SocketStreamReadError,
                                  HTTPMessageException,
                                  CompressionHandlerException
        Implementation of a reader to take input from the configured InputStream. An implementation will construct an instance of HTTPMessage.
        Returns:
        Instance of HTTPMessage constructed from stream result of reading from stream
        Throws:
        SocketStreamReadError - Any exceptions encountered whilst reading from the InputStream
        HTTPMessageException - Any formatting or initialisation exceptions encountered whilst constructing an instance of HTTPMessage
        CompressionHandlerException - Issues encountered whilst attempting to decompress a compressed body

      • futureReadAll

        java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<HTTPMessage<T>> futureReadAll()
        An implementation of an asynchronous read from the configured InputStream. An implementation will construct an instance of HTTPMessage to be supplied as a CompletableFuture
        Returns:
        A CompletableFuture containing an instance of HTTPMessage
